Connecticut Water Service Inc. (CTWS) , a
holding company for a real estate unit and three regulated water
utilities in the U.S. Northeast, said fourth-quarter net income
fell 24 percent.  Net income declined to 16 cents a share from 21 cents the
prior year, according to a company regulatory filing today.  Revenue rose to $19.5 million from $15.4 million. It was
greater than the $18.5 million average of three analystsâ€™
